Document: VisualShaderNodeParticleMeshEmitter
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodeparticlemeshemitter.rst
Summary: Properties defining particle emission behavior from a mesh in visual shaders.

Property: mesh (Mesh): The Mesh that defines emission shape. Default: none. Methods: set_mesh(Mesh) → void, get_mesh() → Mesh.

Property: surface_index (int): Index of the surface that emits particles. Default: 0. Methods: set_surface_index(int) → void, get_surface_index() → int. Note: use_all_surfaces must be false for this to take effect.

Property: use_all_surfaces (bool): If true, particles emit from all surfaces of the mesh. Default: true. Methods: set_use_all_surfaces(bool) → void, is_use_all_surfaces() → bool.